## Common Pitfalls to Avoid

**Buying too much machine:**
Do you really need a 5-ton forklift if you only move light furniture? Higher capacity means higher price and higher installments. Buy what you need for the next 3 years, not 10.

**Ignoring the "Maintenance" cost:**
Financing covers the purchase, but you must still pay for servicing and DOSH certifications (for forklifts). Factor this into your monthly budget.

**Waiting until the last minute:**
If your old forklift is smoking and about to die, don't wait until it stops moving to apply. Apply while it's still working so you don't have "downtime" in your warehouse.

